Two mistakes here:

1. The definition of the enum shouldn&#39;t have `class` in it. As a rule of thumb, the constants should be uppercase.

        enum RoleName {
            WORKER,
            BOSS;
        }

2. `RoleName.Worker.name()` isn&#39;t allowed as a `case` expression since it&#39;s not [a constant expression][1]. You could transform `requestRole.getName()` into a `RoleName` and use it as [a `switch` expression][2].

        switch (RoleName.valueOf(requestRole.getName())) {
            case WORKER: /* ... */ break;
        }


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se13/html/jls-15.html#jls-ConstantExpression
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se13/html/jls-14.html#jls-14.11

